<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 14 at 1:40AM CST  by NWS Eastern ND and Grand Forks</headline>
<description>...ISOLATED NEAR BLIZZARD CONDITIONS WILL AFFECT THE SOUTHERN RED
RIVER VALLEY...
Areas of blowing snow are leading to isolated areas of near blizzard
conditions in open country within the southern Red River Valley this
morning. Persons and vehicles across this area can expect conditions
to suddenly deteriorate to extremely poor visibility for brief
periods of time. These conditions will continue through 5 AM. Rapid
changes in visibility and difficult travel conditions may lead to
accidents. If you are traveling in these conditions, reduce your
speed, don`t use cruise control, and don`t slam on brakes.</description>
